3.4.2. Visual feature extraction
To extract visual representations, the input image is first passed through a CNN backbone to obtain the shared medium feature map ùúë(ùêº) ‚àà Rùë§√ó‚Ñé√óùëê , where h, w and c respectively denote height, width and channel number of the feature map. Then we handle the shared medium feature map separately to get the global and the local visual representations. For the global path, we adopt a Fused Pooling Module to downscale ùúë(ùêº) to ùêæ √ó 1 √ó ùëê:

ùúô(ùêº) = ùê¥ùë£ùëîùëÉ ùëúùëúùëôùëñùëõùëî(ùúë(ùêº)) + ùëÄùëéùë•ùëÉ ùëúùëúùëôùëñùëõùëî(ùúë(ùêº)),

(7)

