with a ELU layer between them to form the medium local visual vectors ùëÄùëñùëâ ‚àà RùëÉ , ùëñ ‚àà {1, 2, ‚Ä¶ , ùêæ}. After that, we concatenate them to form the medium local visual feature matrix ùëÄùëâ ‚àà Rùêæ√óùëÉ .

3.4.3. Local representation vectors converting In order to convert the two medium feature matrices ùëÄùëâ and
ùëÄùëÉ to the corresponding representation vectors, we first adopted the cross-modal attention method to calculate how much each column in one feature matrix is related to the representation vector of the other modality. Taking the local visual representation vector for example, the similarity between each local part column and the sentence representation ùëá ùëÜ is calculated following:

ùõºùëñùëâ

=

ùëíùë•ùëù(ùëêùëúùë†(ùëÄùëñùëâ , ùëá ùëÜ )) ,

